Section-B

1. What is the shape of the following NumPy array?
np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]])
A. (3, 2)
B. (2, 3)
C. (6,)
D. (1, 6)
ans.B. (2, 3)

2. Which operation creates a completely independent copy of a NumPy array?
A. b = a
B. b = a.view()
C. b = a.copy()
D. b = np.assign(a)
ans.C. b = a.copy()

3. Broadcasting works when:
A. Arrays are identical
B. Shapes are compatible
C. Arrays are square
D. Arrays are sorted
ans.B. Shapes are compatible

4. Which operation performs true matrix multiplication?
A. a * b
B. a + b
C. np.matmul(a, b)
D. np.multiply(a, b)
ans.C. np.matmul(a, b)

5. Which attribute returns the memory occupied by a single element in a NumPy array?
A. ndim
B. size
C. itemsize
D. dtype
ans.C. itemsize

6. What will the following statement do?
arr.reshape(-1, 1)
A. Create a row vector
B. Create a column vector
C. Flatten the array
D. Transpose the array
ans.B. Create a column vector

7. Which function generates random integers in NumPy?
A. np.rand()
B. np.randint()
C. np.randomize()
D. np.int()
ans B. np.randint()

9. Which NumPy module contains functions for determinants, inverses, and matrix operations?
A. np.stats
B. np.random
C. np.linalg
D. np.math
ans C. np.linalg

10. Which NumPy feature significantly reduces the need for explicit loops?
A. Broadcasting
B. Printing
C. Indexing
D. Sorting
ans A. Broadcasting

Bonus MCQs (Interview Level)

11. What is the output shape of:
a = np.array([[1], [2], [3]])
b = np.array([10, 20, 30])
a + b
A. (3,)
B. (3,1)
C. (3,3)
D. Error
ans C. (3,3)

12. What happens when you execute:
a = np.array([1, 2, 3])
b = a
b[0] = 100
A. Only b changes
B. Only a changes
C. Both a and b change
D. Error
ans C. Both a and b change

13. Which function creates an identity matrix of size 4×4?
A. np.eye(4)
B. np.zeros((4,4))
C. np.ones((4,4))
D. np.random((4,4))
ans A. np.eye(4)

14. Which axis represents columns?
A. np.eye(4)
B. axis=1
C. axis=2
D. None of the above
ans A. np.eye(4)

15. What is the primary advantage of NumPy vectorized operations?
A. Better formatting
B. Reduced memory usage only
C. Faster execution by avoiding Python loops
D. Easier printing of arrays
ans C. Faster execution by avoiding Python loops
